Package laborator_2.homework

Class Road

java.lang.Object
laborator_2.homework.Road
Direct Known Subclasses:
CountyRoad, ExpressRoad, Freeway
public class Road extends Object
The "Road" class is used to create objects that contain information about a road, from a location to another one, including speedLimit, length, the starting and, ending location.

  • Constructor Details

    • Road

      public Road(double length, int speedLimit, Location locationStart, Location locationEnd)
      Road class constructor. The constructor of the "Road class" is used to create Road objects with a maximum speedLimit, specific length, locationStart and locationEnd. If a road with the same atributes already exists, an error message is displayed and no new location is created. If the length of the road is less than the Euclidean distance between the two locations then an error message is displayed and no new location is created.
      Parameters:
      length - The length of the street.
      speedLimit - The speed limit of the street.
      locationStart - The starting location of the street.
      locationEnd - The end location of the street.

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Object road)
      Checks if two Road objects are equal. Two Road objects are equal if they have the same start and end location, length, and speed limit. If the two locations are reversed, the objects are still considered equal.
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Parameters:
      road - the Road object to compare with the current object
      Returns:
      true if the two objects are equal, false otherwise
